OL,3,CVeteran forced to raid pension for
OL,4,Clifesaving heart surgery
OL,6,FNeil said he felt he had no option but
OL,7,Fto raid his pension pot and pay
OL,8,F#25,000 to have the procedure done
OL,9,Fprivately. Without that cash - Neil's
OL,10,Fstory could have ended very
OL,11,Fdifferently.
OL,13,FHeart disease is one of the country's
OL,14,Fbiggest killers. Six out of then
OL,15,Fhouseholds in the North West will be
OL,16,Fhome to someone with heart disease and
OL,17,Fwaiting times for treatment are at a
OL,18,Frecord high
